    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in SIB2 RRC configuration logging functions\n\n### Summary\nThe RRC UE module contained a race condition in several SIB2 configuration logging functions that could cause incorrect log output when multiple threads accessed these functions simultaneously. The functions used static character buffers that could be overwritten by concurrent calls.\n\nThe race condition affected logging of RACH configuration parameters during cell selection and reconfiguration procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c`: Replaced static character buffers with precomputed static string arrays in SIB2 logging functions:\n  - `SIB2numberOfRA_Preambles`\n  - `SIB2preambleInitialReceivedTargetPower` \n  - `SIB2preambleTransMax`\n  - `SIB2ra_ResponseWindowSize`\n  - `SIB2mac_ContentionResolutionTimer`\n  - `SIB2modificationPeriodCoeff`\n  - `SIB2defaultPagingCycle`\n\nFunctions now return pointers to static const string literals instead of shared buffers, eliminating the race condition while maintaining identical external behavior.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy multithreaded load with multiple UEs performing cell reselection simultaneously, incorrect RACH parameter values were occasionally logged. For example, `preambleTransMax` values would sometimes show \"n200\" when the actual configuration was \"n3\".\n\nThe issue was most reproducible when UEs were rapidly switching between cells with different SIB2 configurations.\n"
}